    "question_id" : 4962361,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>There is none. Either use a <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/List.html\"><code>java.util.List</code></a>*, or you can write your own <code>indexOf()</code>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static &lt;T&gt; int indexOf(T needle, T[] haystack)\n{\n    for (int i=0; i&lt;haystack.length; i++)\n    {\n        if (haystack[i] != null &amp;&amp; haystack[i].equals(needle)\n            || needle == null &amp;&amp; haystack[i] == null) return i;\n    }\n\n    return -1;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p><sub>*you can make one from your array using <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Arrays.html#asList%28T...%29\"><code>Arrays#asList()</code></a></sub></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 184855,
      "reputation" : 10782,
      "user_id" : 421162,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/gfUjq.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Kerem Baydoğan",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/421162/kerem-baydo%c4%9fan"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 81,
    "last_activity_date" : 1428439651,
    "last_edit_date" : 1428439651,
    "creation_date" : 1297370514,
    "answer_id" : 4962437,
    "question_id" : 4962361,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Array has no <code>indexOf()</code> method.</p>\n\n<p>Maybe this Apache Commons Lang <a href=\"http://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/javadocs/api-release/org/apache/commons/lang3/ArrayUtils.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>ArrayUtils</code></a> method is what you are looking for</p>\n\n<pre><code>import org.apache.commons.lang3.ArrayUtils;\n\nString[] colours = { \"Red\", \"Orange\", \"Yellow\", \"Green\" };\n\nint indexOfYellow = ArrayUtils.indexOf(colours, \"Yellow\");\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
