    "question_id" : 4962361,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>int findIndex(int myElement, int[] someArray){\n int index = 0;\n for(int n: someArray){\n   if(myElement == n) return index;\n   else index++;\n }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note: you can use this method for arrays of type int, you can also use this algorithm for other types with minor changes</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6111237,
      "reputation" : 19349,
      "user_id" : 4767498,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 87,
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-u6daZXYwzxs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABI/0xXoH0XUtkc/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "M.kazem Akhgary",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4767498/m-kazem-akhgary"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1543741957,
    "creation_date" : 1543741957,
    "answer_id" : 53578901,
    "question_id" : 4962361,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/4962413/4767498\">Jeffrey Hantin</a>'s answer is good but it has some constraints, if its this do this or else to that...</p>\n\n<p>You can write your own extension method and it always works the way you want.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Lists.indexOf(array, x -&gt; item == x); // compare in the way you want\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And here is your extension</p>\n\n<pre><code>public final class Lists {\n    private Lists() {\n    }\n\n    public static &lt;T&gt; int indexOf(T[] array, Predicate&lt;T&gt; predicate) {\n        for (int i = 0; i &lt; array.length; i++) {\n            if (predicate.test(array[i])) return i;\n        }\n        return -1;\n    }\n\n    public static &lt;T&gt; int indexOf(List&lt;T&gt; list, Predicate&lt;T&gt; predicate) {\n        for (int i = 0; i &lt; list.size(); i++) {\n            if (predicate.test(list.get(i))) return i;\n        }\n        return -1;\n    }\n\n    public interface Predicate&lt;T&gt; {\n        boolean test(T t);\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
